{"id":175,"parent_id":172,"book_id":9398,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":175,"title":"James 4-5: Overcoming Evil in Your Life","subtitle":"","short_title":"James 4-5: Overcoming Evil in Your Life","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-general-epistle-of-james/james-4-5-overcoming-evil-in-your-life","content":[["div",{"id":"container","role":"main"},["div",{"type":"chapter","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-general-epistle-of-james/james-4-5-overcoming-evil-in-your-life"},[".heading",{"id":"head4","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-general-epistle-of-james/james-4-5-overcoming-evil-in-your-life.head4"},["h1","James 4–5"],[".subtitle","Overcoming Evil in Your Life"],[".intro","James gave practical advice for everyday living, like the importance of submitting to God’s will and understanding how wealth can limit spiritual development. His counsel is as important today as when he first wrote it. Of the many ideas in",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/james/4"},"James 4–5"],", note those that would help you most as you strive to live Heavenly Father’s plan."]],[".bodyBlock",[".topic",["h2","Understanding the Scriptures"],[".figure",{"id":"f10","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-general-epistle-of-james/james-4-5-overcoming-evil-in-your-life.f10"},["p"],["h2",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/james/4"},"James 4"]],["p"],["table",["tbody",["tr",["td",["b","Enmity"],"(v. 4)"],["td","Opposed, against, hatred"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Lusteth to envy"],"(v. 5)"],["td","Has jealous desires"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Nigh"],"(v. 8)"],["td","Near"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Heaviness"],"(v. 9)"],["td","Sadness, sorrow"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Vapour"],"(v. 14)"],["td","Mist"],["td"]]]]],[".figure",{"id":"f11","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-general-epistle-of-james/james-4-5-overcoming-evil-in-your-life.f11"},["p"],["h2",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/james/5"},"James 5"]],["p"],["table",["tbody",["tr",["td",["b","Sabaoth"],"(v. 4)"],["td","Hosts, multitudes"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Wanton"],"(v. 5)"],["td","Wasteful in luxurious living"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Husbandman"],"(v. 7)"],["td","Gardener, farmer"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Grudge"],"(v. 9)"],["td","Grumble, complain"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Effectual"],"(v. 16)"],["td","Effective, influential"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Ferven"],"t (v. 16)"],["td","Intense, sincere"],["td"]]]]]],[".topic",["h2","Studying the Scriptures"],["p.para",{"id":"p53","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-general-epistle-of-james/james-4-5-overcoming-evil-in-your-life.p53"},"Do the following activities as you study",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/james/4"},"James 4–5"],"."],[".topic",["h3",["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/icon-a.gif"}],"Write a Prescription"],["p.para",{"id":"p54","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-general-epistle-of-james/james-4-5-overcoming-evil-in-your-life.p54"},"Imagine you are a doctor. Read",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/james/4.1-4"},"James 4:1–4"],"and identify four symptoms people have who suffer from the disease known as “friendship of the world.” Now that you have diagnosed the spiritual disease, read",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/james/4.7-12"},"James 4:7–12"],"and write a prescription that would help people overcome their “friendship of the world” and become healed as a friend of God."]],[".topic",["h3",["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/icon-b.gif"}],"Describe a Priesthood Blessing"],["p.para",{"id":"p55","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-general-epistle-of-james/james-4-5-overcoming-evil-in-your-life.p55"},"Elder Neal A. Maxwell told the following story:"],["p.para",{"id":"p56","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-general-epistle-of-james/james-4-5-overcoming-evil-in-your-life.p56"},"“I first felt the witness of the Spirit in my life around the time my sister was ill. She lay dying of whooping cough, six weeks old. I’d been about 14-years-old. I was a grease monkey [mechanic] at a Greyhound Bus Depot. I came home at three in the morning, saw the lights on. I knew she was ill and said to myself, ‘This is big trouble.’ And when I got inside, she was laying on the round dining room table and had stopped breathing."],["p.para",{"id":"p57","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-general-epistle-of-james/james-4-5-overcoming-evil-in-your-life.p57"},"“Antibiotics were not available. I watched my father, after the manner of the New Testament, bless her by the power of the priesthood, and I saw her begin to breathe again. I knew then the power of the priesthood was real” (“PBS Interview Studies Effect of God in Life,”",["span.emphasis","Church News,"],"31 Aug. 1996, 4)."],[".figure",{"id":"f12","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-general-epistle-of-james/james-4-5-overcoming-evil-in-your-life.f12"},["ol.number",["li",["span.label","1."],["p.para","After reading",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/james/5.14-16"},"James 5:14–16"],", describe what a priesthood blessing is."]],["li",["span.label","2."],["p.para","Briefly write about a time in your life when you received or witnessed a priesthood blessing."]]]]]]],[".resources",[".",{"id":"f13","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-general-epistle-of-james/james-4-5-overcoming-evil-in-your-life.f13"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/p-156-1.gif"}]]]]]],"refs":null}
